formattedAddress: Level 57, Marina Bay Sands Hotel (12A Bayfront Ave)

tip.text: The beer selection is the same as everywhere else. It's not craft, it's all stuff owned by Guinness and the other major breweries. Save your money for the Temple Bar.
They have just three beers, just like the other brewpub (Baku Brewery). The interior is beautiful...industrial and modern.
The outdoor seating is amazing. This is the most beautiful restaurant I've seen in Azerbaijan.

formattedAddress: C. Muntaner, 55 (C. del Consell de Cent)

tip.text: Kind of a dive café, small and cute. The pizza is like a personal pan pizza and took about 10 minutes since it was already made. Cheap wine by the bottle, pizza, pasta and tapas.

venue.name: Kiş Alban kilsəsi | Albanian church of Kish

tip.text: Efes and Erdinger beer, outdoor seating with a fountain view, soft jazz music and free wifi.
It is weird that they serve ALL the drinks (including water) in pairs of 1/2 pint mugs, even if you are alone.
Um, the small wing plate is huge!
The people are super nice and the beer selection is pretty good, plus liquor and wine for your non-beer friends.
